author: gstein
msg: Start cleaning up the Ev1/Ev2 shim code, now that it is fully switched
to change_node. We also have more regularity in paths, so switch path
variable names to better indicate the contents.
* subversion/libsvn_delta/compat.c:
(struct ev2_edit_baton): drop PATHS. tweak CHANGES comment.
(struct path_action, struct copy_args): unused. remove.
(locate_change): strip out management of PATHS.
(get_children): use the CHANGES hash, rather than PATHS. drop
sanitization since we already have a relpath. rename localvar, as
we're getting repos relpaths from the hash
(process_actions): rename param to REPOS_RELPATH to indicate its
contents. drop ACTIONS param. drop path sanitization.
(run_ev2_actions): rename localvar to REPOS_RELPATH. don't bother
with fetching actions from PATHS.
(ev2_add_directory, ev2_add_file): stop creating a COPY_ARGS struct
(svn_delta__delta_from_editor): stop initializing EB->PATHS
(struct editor_baton): drop unused PATHS member
(svn_delta__editor_from_delta): do not initialize unused PATHS
